insert into "books" ("img_url", "publisher", "summary", "title", "year") values ('http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pWgBybLNYGQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Clements Publishing Group', '"In the course of his teaching, Jesus compared the Holy Spirit''s working to the wind: ''You hear the sound of it, but you do not know whence it comes or whither it goes'' (John 3:8). Although the source of the wind lies beyond human understanding, its effects can clearly be seen all around us." Using heartwarming, firsthand illustrations, Kenneth C. Kinghorn unfolds a clear explanation of the Spirit-filled life. Through the Holy Spirit there is unending joy and comfort meant for every individual who is earnest and receptive to a spiritual revival. The author points out that life today brings many demands upon us. Each of us admits that we need "something beyond ourselves. We want solutions that reach down to the root issues of life and offer meaning to us in the inner sanctuary of our souls." Fresh Wind of the Spirit provides an answer for those seeking a renewed zest to live in our hectic and often impersonal world.', 'Fresh Wind of the Spirit', '2002-11-01');
